'''''Halysis''''' is a [[genus]] of [[red algae|red alga]] thought to fall in the [[Coralline algae|coralline]] stem group.  It has only been recovered in thin sections, and thus is only known in two dimensions; however, an interpretation as a sheet of [[Cell (biology)|cells]] rather than a sheet of tubes or a single row of cells is the most plausible.<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Riding | first1 = R. | last2 = Braga | first2 = J. C. | title = ''Halysis'' Høeg, 1932 — An Ordovician coralline red alga? | journal = Journal of Paleontology | volume = 79 | issue = 5 | pages = 835 | year = 2005 | issn = 0022-3360 | doi = 10.1666/0022-3360(2005)079[0835:HHAOCR]2.0.CO;2}}</ref>

