'''Juan Carlos Sánchez Terrones''' (born January 8, 1991 in [[Los Mochis, Sinaloa]], [[Mexico]]) is a [[Mexican people|Mexican]] professional [[Boxing|boxer]] and the former [[International Boxing Federation|IBF]] [[Super Flyweight]] Champion.<ref>http://boxrec.com/list_bouts.php?human_id=480215&cat=boxer</ref>

==Professional career==
His first loss was to the undefeated [[Mexican people|Mexican]], [[Daniel Rosas]], this bout was for the vacant [[World Boxing Council|WBC CABOFE]] [[Super Flyweight]] Championship.<ref>http://boxrec.com/show_display.php?show_id=595562</ref>

In December 2010, Juan Carlos beat the undefeated Juan Francisco Estrada at the Polideportivo Centenario in [[Los Mochis, Sinaloa]], [[Mexico]].<ref>http://boxrec.com/show_display.php?show_id=620107</ref>

===IBF Super Flyweight Championship===
On February 2, 2012 Sánchez upset [[Rodrigo Guerrero]] to win the [[International Boxing Federation|IBF]] [[Super Flyweight]] Championship.<ref>http://boxrec.com/list_bouts.php?human_id=480215&cat=boxer</ref>

